  <description><![CDATA[<p>The best thing about Hotel Catullo is its location. It's in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/59fcac55a66d4666ae4b0cca449364d1}" title="Bardolino">Bardolino</a> right on the harbour and it has fantastic lake views. You're within easy walking distance of everything the town has to offer. Family-run restaurants, busy bars and the stunning lakeside promenade are all on your doorstep. The ferry port is less than a minute down the road, so it's ideal if you want to explore the lake. Regular ferries can take you to nearby towns like <a data-udi="umb://document/0f9f33f516a448a2ab8bda68f2fba594" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0f9f33f516a448a2ab8bda68f2fba594}" title="Peschiera">Peschiera</a> or up to the rugged terrain and medieval castles of <a data-udi="umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce" href="/{localLink:umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce}" title="Malcesine">Malcesine</a>.</p>
<p>This is a family-run hotel so you'll get a warm and friendly welcome. It exudes personality with antique statues, paintings and even the odd Vespa decorating the communal areas. The rooms have a traditional Italian design and every room has a balcony with lake views. There's a small pool at the back of the hotel that gets the sun all day. We love relaxing here with a cocktail from the pool bar! Don't leave without trying the hotel's restaurant, Catullo. It’s where you'll find some of the tastiest pizzas in Bardolino, best enjoyed on sunny terrace beside the promenade.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 45 mins by coach from Verona airport.</p>]]></description>
